Wojciech Szczesny took Arsenal's youngsters under his wing to do a bit of sightseeing in New York.

The Gunners keeper and a host of starlets like Chuba Akpom, Kris Olsson and Francis Coquelin rode the subway before visiting the Top of the Rock in the Rockefeller Centre.

The young Gunners - who also had Nacho Monreal in tow - took in the stunning view of the city from the summit, which stands 70 floors up.

