Arsenal's tour schedule kicks off with an emotional reunion with Gunners icon Thierry Henry as they face the New York Red Bulls.

Gunners boss Arsene Wenger insists Henry still has it - and joked he wanted him to turn out for his  side in the exhibition game. 

Wenger said: ‘I came here with only one striker because I hoped he would play one half for us. He practises with us and is still very sharp and he came back here in very good shape.’

Akpom is the only recognised striker in Arsenal's touring party.

